Summary

Explore mean dp, call rate and Ts/Tv per case.

Exclude cases with mean_dp<20 and call rate <50%:
108_S482_L008 152_S511_L008 306_S410_L008 346_S276_L008 384_S486_L008 498_S507_L008 HG00127

Exclude 2 variants that became uniform or NA after the cases removal
Check that min variants call rate is > 0.85 after the cases removal

Input data: 1.886 vars x 739 cases (541 wecare + 198 nfe)
Output data: 1.884 vars x 732 cases (535 wecare + 197 nfe)

check_TsTv

Needs stringr and TsTv_ratio udf

TsTv.mx <- matrix(ncol=4,nrow=0)
colnames(TsTv.mx) <- c("case","TsTv","Ts","Tv")

for(sample in colnames(gt_chr.mx)){
  
  #sample <- "147_S493_L008"
  #sample <- "108_S482_L008"
  
  # Get and split genotypes
  g <- gt_chr.mx[,sample]
  
  # If at least 100 genotypes are present
  if(sum(!is.na(g))>500){
    
    # Get and parse genotypes
    x <- str_split(g[!is.na(g)], "/")
    y <- t(matrix(unlist(x),nrow=2))
    
    # Calculate TsTv
    Ref <- y[,1]
    Alt <- y[,2]
    z <- TsTv_ratio(Ref,Alt)
  } else {
    
    # No TsTv ratio is calculated if less than 100 genotypes are present
    z <- c(NA,NA,NA)
  }
  
  # Write result
  TsTv.mx <- rbind(TsTv.mx,c(sample,z))

}

# Function to detect uniform numeric vector
uniform_vector.udf <- function(x){
  if(min(x, na.rm=TRUE) == max(x, na.rm=TRUE)){return(TRUE)} else {return(FALSE)}}
